summary:
The Security Council, 
Recalling previous resolutions and statements on Somalia, 
Expressing concern that Al-Shabaab poses a threat to Somalia and the region, 
Acting under Chapter VII, 
1. Extends authorisations until 15 August 2024, as per resolution 2628 (2022) and 2741 (2024); 
2. Authorises up to 12,626 uniformed personnel, including 1,040 police, to ATMIS until 15 August 2024; 
3. Requests the Secretary-General to provide logistical support through UNSOS for: 
   (a) UNSOM on a cost-recovery basis; 
   (b) ATMIS uniformed personnel; 
   (c) up to 85 ATMIS civilians; 
4. Continues provision for up to 20,900 Somali National Army or Police personnel on joint operations with ATMIS until 15 August 2024; 
5. Remains seized of the matter.
